1
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,280
Zhaxi

2
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,840
Zhaxi, come over here quick!

3
00:01:46,239 --> 00:01:47,560
This looks like Tibetan Madder.

4
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:51,760
It really is Tibetan Madder.

5
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,120
It's not yet time

6
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,719
for new branches and leaves to grow.

7
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,599
Its roots are hidden in the moss.

8
00:01:56,959 --> 00:01:58,280
No wonder I didn't see it earlier.

9
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:00,599
The Alizarin content looks pretty high.

10
00:02:01,319 --> 00:02:02,079
Let me take a sample first.

11
00:02:12,919 --> 00:02:13,639
There's more up here.

12
00:02:14,879 --> 00:02:16,319
Is this stuff really that amazing?

13
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:18,199
A Quaternary glacial relict species.

14
00:02:18,439 --> 00:02:19,680
A living fossil in the gene pool.

15
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,360
Its medicinal value is immeasurable.

16
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:25,319
There's more over there.

17
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:28,639
There's a whole patch over there.

18
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,360
Nana, are you okay?

19
00:02:49,599 --> 00:02:50,520
It'll be dark soon.

20
00:02:51,439 --> 00:02:52,639
We need to get out of here quickly.

21
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,240
Otherwise, it'll be dangerous.

22
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:56,759
Give me the bag.

23
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,560
Listen to me.

24
00:03:02,759 --> 00:03:03,319
Come on.

25
00:03:04,599 --> 00:03:05,479
Follow me.

26
00:03:11,159 --> 00:03:12,000
I'll go collect over there first.

27
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:12,960
Okay.

28
00:03:18,479 --> 00:03:19,039
Dr. Meiduo!

29
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,240
The blinding fog!

30
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,080
It's getting cold. Put this on.

31
00:04:09,639 --> 00:04:10,000
Here.

32
00:04:10,599 --> 00:04:12,080
It's hot. Drink up.

33
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,160
Brown sugar water.

34
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:23,399
When you had a fever as a kid,

35
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,120
I'd give you this to drink.

36
00:04:28,879 --> 00:04:29,560
Actually,

37
00:04:30,079 --> 00:04:31,600
I've been watching over you two all along.

38
00:04:33,079 --> 00:04:34,079
When you went to college,

39
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,240
your very first ad gig,

40
00:04:37,079 --> 00:04:37,839
when you got sick,

41
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:40,839
I knew about all of it.

42
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,439
Every post you wrote on Weibo,

43
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:45,600
I read every single one.

44
00:04:46,519 --> 00:04:47,319
Back then,

45
00:04:47,959 --> 00:04:49,360
the signal in these mountains was bad.

46
00:04:50,279 --> 00:04:51,639
So I'd walk a long way

47
00:04:52,319 --> 00:04:53,279
and climb to the mountaintop.

48
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,360
Anything you posted,

49
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:58,079
I'd screenshot, download, and save it.

50
00:04:58,959 --> 00:05:00,279
At night, whenever I had time,

51
00:05:01,199 --> 00:05:02,199
I'd open it up and look at it again.

52
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:05,360
Don't you...

53
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,839
want to ask how my mom's doing?

54
00:05:12,839 --> 00:05:13,399
Is she...

55
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:15,360
doing okay?

56
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:18,639
She's doing great.

57
00:05:20,079 --> 00:05:21,639
Last year she moved into a bigger place,

58
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,120
the kind with a balcony for growing flowers.

59
00:05:24,879 --> 00:05:27,480
She always wanted a balcony for flowers.

60
00:05:29,879 --> 00:05:30,560
She's retired now.

61
00:05:33,079 --> 00:05:35,519
Every day she goes dancing with her friends,

62
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:36,879
travels around.

63
00:05:38,519 --> 00:05:39,160
She's doing great.

64
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:43,959
That man,

65
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:46,680
is he good to her?

66
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,079
Yeah, he's good to her.

67
00:05:51,959 --> 00:05:53,040
He's a teacher.

68
00:05:54,279 --> 00:05:55,240
He's retired too.

69
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,639
They often go grocery shopping together,

70
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,839
cook, and take walks.

71
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,560
They're a good match.

72
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:04,240
That's good.

73
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:08,839
That's all you've got to say?

74
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,639
What I couldn't give her,

75
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:11,800
someone else can.

76
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,040
That's good.

77
00:06:19,839 --> 00:06:21,439
After I paid off those debts,

78
00:06:22,319 --> 00:06:23,399
I kept thinking about you two.

79
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,279
Walking out the way I did back then,

80
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:27,639
I feel like

81
00:06:30,439 --> 00:06:31,839
I really owe you both so much.

82
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:34,720
Even though you got divorced,

83
00:06:36,079 --> 00:06:37,199
at first, Mom

84
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:39,639
kept waiting for you.

85
00:06:41,639 --> 00:06:42,920
She waited eight years for you.

86
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,959
You didn't even call once.

87
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,639
You know why I came here?

88
00:06:52,199 --> 00:06:53,279
I just wanted to ask you straight up.

89
00:06:54,399 --> 00:06:56,240
How could you just leave for twenty years?

90
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,800
How could you make a woman wait eight years?

91
00:07:03,199 --> 00:07:05,199
How could you owe money and never come back?

92
00:07:13,879 --> 00:07:15,199
My mom asked me to tell you,

93
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,319
she's doing just fine.

94
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:21,600
Don't worry about her.

95
00:07:22,839 --> 00:07:24,079
Come back whenever you want.

96
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,160
There's still a place for you at home.

97
00:07:27,959 --> 00:07:29,079
Not to live with her,

98
00:07:29,639 --> 00:07:30,519
but to live with me.

99
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,160
Even though she has a new family now,

100
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,800
she said,

101
00:07:38,279 --> 00:07:39,279
"You're my dad.

102
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,920
That's a fact that'll never change."

103
00:07:51,839 --> 00:07:52,920
The brown sugar water's not bad.

104
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,120
Tastes just like it did when I was little.

105
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:01,439
Oh, by the way.

106
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:03,839
Stop sending money home from now on.

107
00:08:04,759 --> 00:08:05,480
My mom doesn't need it.

108
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,360
If you really want to take some responsibility,

109
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:09,800
send it to me instead.

110
00:08:10,519 --> 00:08:11,639
I don't need much.

111
00:08:12,319 --> 00:08:12,920
Just enough to get by.

112
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,560
What are you laughing at?

113
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:17,720
You,

114
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:19,240
you're just like your mom.

115
00:08:19,839 --> 00:08:21,160
Gruff but kind-hearted.

116
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,079
Give me another cup of brown sugar water.

117
00:08:26,319 --> 00:08:26,839
You got it.

118
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:27,759
As much as you want.

119
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:32,600
Here.

120
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,120
Drink up.

121
00:09:05,039 --> 00:09:05,600
Zhaxi.

122
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,399
The fog seems to be lifting.

123
00:09:12,279 --> 00:09:13,200
Brother Jimei, Brother Jimei.

124
00:09:14,159 --> 00:09:14,759
Copy that.

125
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:15,960
The fog's cleared.

126
00:09:16,519 --> 00:09:17,639
But just to be safe,

127
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,320
let's rest a bit before heading down.

128
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,480
Okay, okay, okay.

129
00:09:20,799 --> 00:09:21,759
We'll talk again soon.

130
00:09:31,559 --> 00:09:32,159
What are you looking at?

131
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,480
My Aba told me

132
00:09:36,039 --> 00:09:38,039
everyone has a star up in the sky.

133
00:09:39,159 --> 00:09:40,360
If you do something good,

134
00:09:40,919 --> 00:09:41,799
it shines a little brighter.

135
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,000
If you do something bad,

136
00:09:44,679 --> 00:09:45,679
it dims a little.

137
00:09:48,639 --> 00:09:49,720
That's just a story for kids.

138
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:52,919
I know.

139
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:56,399
But I still want to believe it.

140
00:10:00,639 --> 00:10:01,279
Believe what?

141
00:10:02,919 --> 00:10:04,679
That what you do will be remembered.

142
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,679
Just like those plants.

143
00:10:07,159 --> 00:10:08,200
They can't speak either,

144
00:10:08,879 --> 00:10:09,759
but if you treat them well,

145
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,519
they'll surely remember.

146
00:10:14,519 --> 00:10:16,080
Am I talking too much?

147
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:18,759
Not at all.

148
00:10:21,639 --> 00:10:22,120
It's nice.
